The impact of Zipf parameter α and Γ to RTR in ER

model is shown in Fig. 31. It indicates that RTR is not re-

lated to Γ, which is the maximum copies of cached content

sliced to each content in the UE level, while it depends on

the popularity of contents because each content will be

cached in the SBS level for some time. When α = 0.5, the

RTR is about 70%, in other words, about 70% of the re-

quests can be hit in either SBS level or UE level.

